descp2: boolean, default=False Whether score_func takes a continuous decision certainty. This only works for binary classification using estimators that have either a decision_function or predict_proba method. If True, for binary `y_true`, the score function is supposed to accept a 1D `y_pred` (i.e., probability of the positive class or the decision function, shape `(n_samples,)`). For example ``average_precision`` or the area under the roc curve can not be computed using discrete predictions alone.
